    "Bias and SafetyBoth OpenAI and Google prioritize mitigating harmful biases in their language models.",
    "Nonetheless, given the inherent biases present in the training data reflecting real-world human biases, this remains a persistent challenge.",
    "OpenAI adopts a cautious approach when generating outputs that may be sensitive or potentially harmful.",
    "Similarly, Google adheres to its 'do no harm' principle, emphasizing safety.",
    "However, the risk of producing biased or offensive content persists with both models, underscoring the importance of recognizing their limitations."
